111
00:07:06,188 --> 00:07:08,188
This is natural stuff.

112
00:07:08,188 --> 00:07:10,688
Right, Mr. Detective. Don't you think so too?

113
00:07:10,688 --> 00:07:12,088
Oh, well...

114
00:07:12,088 --> 00:07:13,988
I really can't tell myself...

115
00:07:16,688 --> 00:07:18,417
Dad?

116
00:07:18,417 --> 00:07:21,488
Natural or artificial, you say?

117
00:07:21,488 --> 00:07:25,888
-Who cares? -Who cares?

118
00:07:25,888 --> 00:07:27,788
It's pretty important, I'd say.

119
00:07:27,788 --> 00:07:28,988
I see.

120
00:07:28,988 --> 00:07:31,088
So, is it that you want to make an impression on me

121
00:07:31,088 --> 00:07:33,188
that the boy she's looking for

122
00:07:33,188 --> 00:07:35,388
is knowledgeable about the sea and fish and likes sushi.

123
00:07:35,388 --> 00:07:38,437
Is that what you're trying to get me to see?

124
00:07:38,437 --> 00:07:40,088
Oh, no.

125
00:07:40,088 --> 00:07:41,688
Well, I guess it can't be helped

126
00:07:41,688 --> 00:07:45,388
because 1 billion yen is hanging out there.

127
00:07:45,388 --> 00:07:49,088
Talking of sushi, when that boy bought the pack of sushi,

128
00:07:49,088 --> 00:07:50,988
what did the boy do after doing so?

129
00:07:50,988 --> 00:07:52,988
The change was 100 yen more than what it was supposed to be,

130
00:07:52,988 --> 00:07:55,388
so I went to return it.

131
00:07:55,388 --> 00:07:59,288
I can't take what's not mine.

132
00:07:59,288 --> 00:08:01,388
That's strange.

133
00:08:01,388 --> 00:08:03,088
What is?

134
00:08:03,088 --> 00:08:05,388
Well... the honest boy who said that

135
00:08:05,388 --> 00:08:08,488
he can't accept what's not his

136
00:08:08,488 --> 00:08:11,688
is obviously trying to take off with 1 billion yen

137
00:08:11,688 --> 00:08:14,473
that should be going to someone else.

138
00:08:15,388 --> 00:08:18,477
What're you talking about?

139
00:08:18,477 --> 00:08:20,888
Kurumi is saying that she's going to give the 1 billion away

140
00:08:20,888 --> 00:08:24,483
as a token of her appreciation to the person who risked his own life

141
00:08:24,483 --> 00:08:27,588
to save her from a traffic accident.

142
00:08:27,588 --> 00:08:30,488
What's wrong with accepting it?

143
00:08:30,488 --> 00:08:32,888
You saw when taking a bath with me didn't you,

144
00:08:32,888 --> 00:08:35,288
the scar from the accident back then.

145
00:08:35,288 --> 00:08:38,497
No, the scar on my back

146
00:08:38,497 --> 00:08:41,188
is indeed the scar I got during the accident.

147
00:08:41,188 --> 00:08:46,188
True, you had a large scar about 30 cm long,

148
00:08:46,188 --> 00:08:50,788
but that is again exactly what made me doubt you.

149
00:08:51,788 --> 00:08:55,588
Kurumi answered the interview on TV, didn't she?

150
00:08:55,588 --> 00:08:58,788
That the scar extended from one end to the other.

151
00:08:58,788 --> 00:09:00,888
She doesn't remember if the scar was on the chest or back,

152
00:09:00,888 --> 00:09:03,188
but it was a big scar.

153
00:09:03,188 --> 00:09:04,523
She said she was sure of that.

154
00:09:04,523 --> 00:09:08,088
Then, how old were you then?

155
00:09:08,088 --> 00:09:11,288
Around 2nd or 3rd grade of elementary school.

156
00:09:11,288 --> 00:09:14,533
Really? If the boy was in 2nd or 3rd grade of elementary,

157
00:09:14,533 --> 00:09:18,888
a scar reaching from side to side would be about 15 cm...

158
00:09:18,888 --> 00:09:21,088
Well. I guess...

159
00:09:21,088 --> 00:09:24,088
When I first got the scar, it was about that long, but...

160
00:09:24,088 --> 00:09:26,888
As I got older and my body got bigger,

161
00:09:26,888 --> 00:09:29,188
my scar got bigger too.

162
00:09:30,188 --> 00:09:32,551
Don't you know?

163
00:09:32,551 --> 00:09:36,188
Scars don't get larger even if a person grows up.

164
00:09:36,188 --> 00:09:38,088
-What? -What?

165
00:09:38,088 --> 00:09:40,888
If you get a scar that's 15 cm,

166
00:09:40,888 --> 00:09:43,488
the scar stays the same size until you die.

167
00:09:43,488 --> 00:09:47,088
Well, I was pretty big for my age.

168
00:09:47,088 --> 00:09:48,567
Me too.

169
00:09:48,567 --> 00:09:50,288
Mr. Kusumoto.

170
00:09:50,288 --> 00:09:54,888
Didn't you say that you were very thin when you were a child?

171
00:09:54,888 --> 00:09:57,288
I did...

172
00:09:57,288 --> 00:10:00,088
He probably said he was skinny

173
00:10:00,088 --> 00:10:01,688
after hearing that the boy she's looking for

174
00:10:01,688 --> 00:10:03,788
was nicknamed Gari.

175
00:10:03,788 --> 00:10:06,188
He probably mistook it for "gari-gari" which means skinny.

176
00:10:06,188 --> 00:10:08,288
He was actually nicknamed Gari

177
00:10:08,288 --> 00:10:11,688
because he was a bookworm.

178
00:10:11,688 --> 00:10:14,288
Gari because he was a bookworm?

179
00:10:14,288 --> 00:10:15,688
Do you know?

180
00:10:15,688 --> 00:10:20,599
When that boy ate fried noodles at the beach house,

181
00:10:20,599 --> 00:10:23,888
he put a lot of red ginger on it.

182
00:10:23,888 --> 00:10:25,588
What's that about?

183
00:10:25,588 --> 00:10:27,988
I don't know about it.

184
00:10:27,988 --> 00:10:30,609
It's only natural that you don't know about it.

185
00:10:30,609 --> 00:10:32,888
I heard about it for the first time today too.

186
00:10:32,888 --> 00:10:34,988
It's a trump card.

187
00:10:35,988 --> 00:10:38,617
Don't you understand yet?

188
00:10:38,617 --> 00:10:42,188
The boy liked ginger ale,

189
00:10:42,188 --> 00:10:44,988
bought sushi packs often

190
00:10:44,988 --> 00:10:48,088
and used to put a lot of red ginger on his fried noodles.

191
00:10:48,088 --> 00:10:52,388
I see. That boy liked ginger.

192
00:10:52,388 --> 00:10:55,088
There's ginger in ginger ale

193
00:10:55,088 --> 00:10:57,088
and the ginger that comes with sushi

194
00:10:57,088 --> 00:11:00,288
is ginger marinated in sugar and vinegar.

195
00:11:00,288 --> 00:11:01,888
Which means that the reason

196
00:11:01,888 --> 00:11:03,088
the boy got the nickname Gari was because...

197
00:11:03,088 --> 00:11:04,643
Yes, that's right.

198
00:11:04,643 --> 00:11:08,647
He was probably called Gari because he loved ginger.

199
00:11:08,647 --> 00:11:10,288
That's right, isn't it?

200
00:11:10,288 --> 00:11:12,651
You didn't even bother to eat the sushi

201
00:11:12,651 --> 00:11:15,088
but went right for the ginger and ate it all up,

202
00:11:15,088 --> 00:11:17,588
didn't you, Mr. Hoya?

203
00:11:19,488 --> 00:11:20,659
No way.

204
00:11:20,659 --> 00:11:22,661
You mean the real guy was here?

205
00:11:22,661 --> 00:11:27,588
Yes. He has a scar about 15 cm on his back too.

206
00:11:27,588 --> 00:11:30,088
So, there's probably no mistake about it.

207
00:11:30,088 --> 00:11:32,671
