209
00:11:36,188 --> 00:11:39,388
I can't accept that money.

210
00:11:39,388 --> 00:11:43,788
Because if I didn't tell her to stay,

211
00:11:43,788 --> 00:11:47,788
she may have not gotten into the accident.

212
00:11:47,788 --> 00:11:49,988
That's why I decided to watch over her

213
00:11:49,988 --> 00:11:51,288
without revealing my identity.

214
00:11:51,288 --> 00:11:53,088
But, it seems that you couldn't do so

215
00:11:53,088 --> 00:11:55,488
without revealing your true identity.

216
00:11:55,488 --> 00:11:57,288
Do you know why?

217
00:11:57,288 --> 00:11:59,488
Kurumi who knew that you're the type

218
00:11:59,488 --> 00:12:02,701
that would never accept what is not yours,

219
00:12:02,701 --> 00:12:05,488
went on air and publicized

220
00:12:05,488 --> 00:12:07,588
that she wanted to give you the billion yen?

221
00:12:08,707 --> 00:12:10,709
It's because she wanted you,

222
00:12:10,709 --> 00:12:13,688
who was right beside her to come out on your own.

223
00:12:13,688 --> 00:12:15,488
And to tell you to not publicize something like that

224
00:12:15,488 --> 00:12:18,717
because it may bring about imposters.

225
00:12:19,988 --> 00:12:22,721
Then... Kurumi knew, after all.

226
00:12:22,721 --> 00:12:24,988
Yes, she was aware

227
00:12:24,988 --> 00:12:29,988
that Mr. Hoya was the boy she had known back then.

228
00:12:29,988 --> 00:12:32,188
That's why she made him wash my back in the bath tub

229
00:12:32,188 --> 00:12:34,733
where the air conditioner was out of order.

230
00:12:34,733 --> 00:12:38,388
She didn't say anything about the red ginger till today.

231
00:12:38,388 --> 00:12:40,739
She served sushi as a late-night meal.

232
00:12:40,739 --> 00:12:43,988
She did all this to drop hints at me.

233
00:12:43,988 --> 00:12:47,188
So, what now, Mr. Hoya?

234
00:12:47,188 --> 00:12:50,288
Kurumi is waiting in her room.

235
00:12:52,751 --> 00:12:55,588
But... Well...

236
00:12:55,588 --> 00:12:57,288
I...

237
00:12:57,288 --> 00:12:59,288
You'll be fine.

238
00:12:59,288 --> 00:13:02,788
I'll go tell the lady for you in your place.

239
00:13:03,888 --> 00:13:07,188
If you like, shall I go tell her for you?

240
00:13:07,188 --> 00:13:09,388
I really don't want people who are just after the money

241
00:13:09,388 --> 00:13:11,288
lying and saying that they are the ones

242
00:13:11,288 --> 00:13:12,771
that she is looking for besides.

243
00:13:14,773 --> 00:13:18,777
Okay. I'll go tell her myself.

244
00:13:27,388 --> 00:13:29,388
He seems to have been urged to do what he has to do.

245
00:13:29,388 --> 00:13:30,789
Yes.

246
00:13:30,789 --> 00:13:37,088
Jeepers. I'd like to tell the truth if I could, but can't.

247
00:13:37,088 --> 00:13:38,788
Just who are talking about?

248
00:13:41,288 --> 00:13:43,088
Kamen Yaiba.

249
00:13:43,088 --> 00:13:45,488
He can't afford to have people know his true identity.

250
00:13:46,588 --> 00:13:48,588
Then, I guess I'll be going.

251
00:13:48,588 --> 00:13:50,388
Bye.

252
00:13:52,811 --> 00:13:55,488
Hold it, will you?

253
00:13:55,488 --> 00:13:57,088
Police?

254
00:13:57,088 --> 00:13:59,288
I... I was just joking.

255
00:13:59,288 --> 00:14:01,088
I had a scar on my chest

256
00:14:01,088 --> 00:14:02,821
that I got when I got hurt surfing, so...

257
00:14:02,821 --> 00:14:05,388
No, the one that we want

258
00:14:05,388 --> 00:14:08,088
is the guy with the large scar on his back.

259
00:14:08,088 --> 00:14:09,388
You. That is.

260
00:14:10,488 --> 00:14:12,388
Because after all,

261
00:14:12,388 --> 00:14:16,088
that wound is the straight-line scar

262
00:14:16,088 --> 00:14:19,988
what Superintendent Matsumoto left on the serial killer 20 years ago

263
00:14:19,988 --> 00:14:22,588
when he cornered the culprit.

264
00:14:22,588 --> 00:14:23,788
What?

